.TH "ubi_volume_notify" 9 "ubi_volume_notify" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
ubi_volume_notify \- send a volume change notification.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" ubi_volume_notify
.BI "(struct ubi_device *ubi "  ","
.BI "struct ubi_volume *vol "  ","
.BI "int ntype "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "ubi" 12
UBI device description object
.IP "vol" 12
volume description object of the changed volume
.IP "ntype" 12
notification type to send (UBI_VOLUME_ADDED, etc)
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This is a helper function which notifies all subscribers about a volume
change event (creation, removal, re-sizing, re-naming, updating). Returns
zero in case of success and a negative error code in case of failure.
